  "prompt": "Was Donald Trump popular in high school?",
  "response": "Donald Trump attended high school at the New York Military Academy (NYMA) in Cornwall, New York, after transferring from the Kew-Forest School in Queens at the age of 13. During his time at NYMA, Trump was known for his competitive nature and strong leadership qualities. He excelled in sports, particularly in baseball and football, and held positions of responsibility within the school's structure.\n\nReports from classmates and biographical accounts suggest that Trump was both a prominent and sometimes contentious figure among his peers. While some viewed him as a charismatic leader, others noted that his assertive and competitive demeanor could lead to conflicts. Overall, it appears that Trump was a noticeable and influential presence at NYMA, garnering attention and recognition from fellow students and faculty alike.\n\nIt's important to recognize that individual experiences and perceptions can vary, and assessments of his popularity during high school may differ based on personal interactions and perspectives.",
